    <node id="1. Teachers will have a significant level of discretion in determining which individual children are included as &quot;vulnerable&quot; and eligible for support during school closures. Kirsty Williams AM, the Education Minister, emphasized that teachers know their pupils best and encouraged headteachers to include children who may not be obviously in need but would still benefit from additional support. This sentiment was echoed by Suzy Davies AM, who recognized the professional judgment of individual teachers in this matter. Constraints on this discretion will be minimal, as the Welsh government has stated that they will not put any constraints on teachers trying to identify and support vulnerable children." />
