    <node id="1. The Welsh Government is using various platforms of communication to disseminate information regarding the pandemic to parents. They are utilizing informal methods and a systematic approach via individual directors and schools. A dedicated website page has been set up by the Welsh Government with relevant information about COVID-19, and they are working on creating a frequently asked education questions page for updates.&#10;2. Schools have already started taking initiatives to communicate with parents about their needs. For instance, some schools have sent out questionnaires asking parents if they consider themselves key workers or work in the NHS so that arrangements can be made for their children.&#10;3. However, the Welsh Government has not explicitly mentioned any specific plans to directly communicate to parents about ensuring that at-risk children do not fall through the gaps during the pandemic. It is likely that this information will also be disseminated through existing communication channels and platforms.&#10;4. The cascading of information to schools will continue to be done through individual directors, who are expected to work in conjunction with social services directors to ensure that none of these children fall through the gaps." />
