feguarding arrangements require their presence at school, and those needs must be addressed as well.&#10;3. The Welsh government has stated that they will not put any constraints on teachers trying to identify and support vulnerable children, giving headteachers and teachers significant discretion in determining eligibility for special provisions.&#10;4. Local governments are working with social services departments and individual schools to identify at-risk children, ensuring that up-to-date registers and plans are in place for their continued support during school closures.">
