eration, to help ensure consistency across different schools and regions. This can help minimize disparities in assessment outcomes among various demographic groups.&#10;5. Monitor and evaluate: Continuously monitor the implementation of the modulated arrangement and evaluate its impact on assessment outcomes and student confidence. Adjust the approach as needed based on feedback and data analysis to further promote fairness and consistency.&#10;6. Communicate transparently: Ensure that all stakeholders, including parents, teachers, and students, are well-informed about the grading process and the measures being taken to maintain consistent standards while promoting fairness. Transparent communication can help increase trust and confidence in the awarded grades.">
