igorous standards and addressing potential sources of bias.&#10;4. It is essential to recognize that the current situation may exacerbate existing disparities, as highlighted by Helen Mary Jones AM regarding the National Union of Students' concerns about underperformance among certain demographic groups. The modulated arrangement must take these challenges into account to ensure a fair and accurate grading process for all students.&#10;5. The involvement of Qualifications Wales and the WJEC in designing and implementing this modulated arrangement will be crucial, as they are responsible for overseeing the assessment and grading process. As Kirsty Williams AM stated, she has confidence that these organizations will develop a fair and equitable approach to determining grades while respecting their professional autonomy and expertise.">
