es: Formal NHS counselling services will be available for students who require more intensive mental health support during school closures. This provision ensures that students can still access professional mental health care despite not attending school in person. Although the text does not explicitly mention staff's access to NHS counselling services, it is reasonable to infer that these resources are available for both students and staff.&#10;&#10;4. Guidance on Referrals: While there is no clear guidance yet on how the process of evaluating referrals for additional learning needs pupils will continue once the situation improves, the Welsh Government acknowledges the need to address this matter and ensure that false assurances are not given if the situation on the ground does not allow for a normal evaluation process.">
